text.280:
Clooney: I think we are asking a lot of journalists. I think you're incredibly courageous, but you shouldn't need to be this courageous. It's too much to ask. It's too much pressure on people like you, and I think that's why the system has to change.

https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.281:
Clooney: And the other side of this case is the government, that controls the police, and controls the army, and controls the prosecutors, and potentially controls the courts.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.282:
Clooney: It's not a fair contest. You know, you have the truth on your side, but your foe is the most powerful person in the country.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.283:
Clooney: If you can be taken away and handcuffed and silenced, then every other journalist in the country knows what they need to do to stay safe. 

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.284:
Clooney: I do feel pressure when I work on cases like yours. You know, to some degree, your case does keep me up at night. And it should, because you might be the one in the dark, but it's actually democracy that's on trial.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.285:
Ressa: Because I know that, you know, God forbid, if something happens, and I tell you this all the time, I know you're there. What kind of pressure does that put on you?

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.286:
Ressa: I know how powerful a defender you are, and we in Rappler are just so lucky to have you on our side. You taking my case helps give me the courage to do what we're doing, to continue standing up to power.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.287:
Clooney: I think we both feel very strongly that journalism is the lifeblood of democracy, and that this is something we have to continue to fight for.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.288:
Clooney: I feel so honored to get this award, the Committee to Protect Journalists does incredible work. I couldn't do my work without them, and I rely on their data, I brainstorm with them.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.289:
Ressa: So, Amal, tonight, you are getting the Committee to Protect Journalists’ Gwen Ifill Press Freedom Award. What does this mean to you?

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.290:
Clooney: And so I think journalists have a part to play, lawyers have a part to play, senators have a part to play.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.291:
Clooney: You know, they're becoming more creative in their methods. And so we need to become more savvy in our response.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.292:
Clooney: But the more I see autocratic regimes becoming determined to silence those who disagree with them, to silence those who expose the truth, or corruption, or things that embarrass them, the more determined we have to be.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.293:
Clooney: And you can't defend human rights if journalists can't do their work. You can't defend democracy if you don't have a thriving and independent media.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.294:
Clooney: You asked me why I focus on journalists; I didn't start my career thinking I'm going to focus on cases involving journalists. I decided to focus my career on cases involving human rights.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.295:
Clooney: I don't know. I mean, I would ask you the same question. It never occurs to me to do otherwise. I suppose [hope is] the default.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.296:
Ressa: Thank you for that. We are so much better, because you do what you do. But when you're facing such seemingly hopeless cases, where this amount, where does hope come from for you?

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.297:
Clooney: Today, in 2020, I see in far too many places, those who are committing human rights abuses are free, and those who are reporting on them are in prison, and I will continue to focus on trying to tackle both problems.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.298:
Clooney: But I think another part of it, though, is, frankly, anger. I think anger drives a lot of what I do, because when I read about what's happening in many places in the world, I just feel a sense of outrage…

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.299:
Clooney: And I was lucky enough, my family was able to leave the country, and we moved to the UK as refugees, and from them, anything was possible.

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
text.300:
Clooney: I think one of the reasons I do it is because I know how lucky I am. I was born in Lebanon, at a time when that country was going through a civil war. 

#IPFA: https://t.co/VVCUxmgUUn
